</P>
<P>
Jenny Craig Inc., up $1.375 at $3.125
</P>
<P>
   The nation's second largest operator of weight loss centers said
its founders have offered to buy the one-third stake in Jenny Craig
they don't already own for $25.6 million, or $3.75 a share. The
company has been hurt by increasing competition and declining
profits.
</P>
<P>
Primark Corp., up $8.25 at $37.25
</P>
<P>
   Thomson Corp. is paying $842 million in cash to buy Primark,
another provider of professional and financial information. Thomson
is paying $38 per share for Primark, a 31 percent premium over the
company's closing share price of $29 Friday.
