<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits East Taiwan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- A moderate earthquake rattled northeastern
Taiwan on Tuesday morning, seismologists said. No damage or
injuries were immediately reported.
</P>
<P>
   The 4.8-magnitude quake's epicenter was 21 miles south of Ilan
city, the Central Weather Bureau said. Ilan is about 60 miles south
of the capital, Taipei.
</P>
<P>
   Located along the earthquake-prone Pacific Rim and crisscrossed
by 51 fault lines, Taiwan is hit by scores of earthquakes each
year, but few cause serious damage.
</P>
<P>
   A 7.6-magnitude quake devastated central Taiwan in September,
killing about 2,400 people and destroying thousands of homes. Since
the earthquake, more than 12,000 aftershocks and minor tremors have
rattled the island. Most have been harmless.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
